  "body": "<!--ðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž\r\n\r\nHellooo! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nThanks for taking the time to file a tracking issue for your new feature. These issues really help\r\nus track progress of features as they work their way through development. Be sure to review \r\nshared/featureconfig/README.md for the latest documentation around feature flags.\r\n\r\nðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž-->\r\n\r\n# ðŸ¦„ Feature Tracking\r\n\r\npart of #10242\r\n\r\n**Current status** (opt-in or opt-out): \r\n\r\n**Opt-in feature flag name**:\r\n\r\n**Opt-out feature flag name**: \r\n\r\n### Feature Description\r\n\r\nPost merge, Eth-Stakers would like to earn rewards ( via gas fees) on particular transactions when proposing ( currently only earning rewards from the protocol itself and not on gas fees). This requires stakers to provide an eth1 account ( the fee recipient) to the validator client either as a catch-all ( all validators default to a particular eth1 account) or unique for each validator key. \r\n\r\n### Flow\r\nconfig -> validator client -> beacon node  sets the configuration in cache\r\nvalidator client get block -> beacon node get block with fee recipient -> execution client\r\n\r\n## config json structure based on [teku implementation](https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/4894)\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"proposer_config\": {\r\n    \"0xa057816155ad77931185101128655c0191bd0214c201ca48ed887f6c4c6adf334070efcd75140eada5ac83a92506dd7a\": {\r\n      \"fee_recipient\": \"0x50155530FCE8a85ec7055A5F8b2bE214B3DaeFd3\",\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  \"default_config\": {\r\n    \"fee_recipient\": \"0x6e35733c5af9B61374A128e6F85f553aF09ff89A\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nproposer_config is optional\r\ndefault_config is mandatory\r\nfee_recipient is mandatory in each config\r\n\r\n### Tasks\r\n\r\n- [x] `fee-recipient-config-file` flag for fee recipient to provide config file location from validator client cli \r\n- [x] `fee-recipient-config-url` flg for fee recipient to provide config file via url( api call) from validator client cli \r\n- [x] `suggested-fee-recipient` to set default fee recipient from validator client cli\r\n- [x] `suggested-fee-recipient` to set default fee recipient from beacon node cli\r\n- [ ] flags to update fee recipient config from cli\r\n- [x] a default 0 address is set if the config is not defined along with loud logs\r\n- [x] BEACON API to see fee recipient cache ( [prepare beacon proposer api](https://github.com/ethereum/beacon-APIs/pull/178))\r\n- [ ] trigger fee recipient update when using the fall back node\r\n- [x] update prepare beacon proposer API for [Flashbots MEV Issue](https://github.com/ethereum/beacon-APIs/pull/206)\r\n- [x] documentation\r\n- [x] e2e tests\r\nThis issue should be closed after all of the above tasks are complete.\r\n- [x] Fee recipient Spec for Keymanager API ( https://github.com/ethereum/keymanager-APIs)\r\n- [x] Fee Recipient API implementation\r\n\r\n",
